    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>People in medieval Germany and later who were appointed as the judicial and military representatives of the king in a burg, which was a fortified town. Eventually the title became hereditary and was associated with not only the burg but also the surrounding domain.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
